Durban - Police are still searching for an awaiting trial prisoner who escaped from Westville Prison on Monday. According to KZN police spokesperson Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane, the suspect has been identified as Njabulo Lucky Mbatha. The 32-year-old who faces charges of housebreaking and theft managed to escape at around 12 pm. "The awaiting trial prisoner escaped from prison while workers were busy with the construction at the prison." Zwane said a case of escaping from lawful custody has been opened at the Westville police station for investigation. He said no other prisoners escaped and that police were still searching for the suspect by Tuesday. If anyone has any information they can contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111. In July last year Westville prison’s Medium A section which houses awaiting trial prisoners had been on lock-down after police were tipped-off about a prison break being planned. Correctional services officials searched prisoners after it was alleged that the explosives and firearms had made its way into the prison facility. Daily News